<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.011/3.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s January 18, 11 a.m. Suggest you emphasize need for proper
                            provision regarding registration of voters as protection against fraud
                            at the polls. Measures should be adopted to preclude governors from
                            coercing voters. Limitations applied to authority of governors in this
                            and other matters should also apply to authority of President.</p>
                        <p>Department will gladly consider any suggestions you have to make.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>